 inquiries into online/offline languages in society, language users, language learners and language teachers who may operate ‘between’ languages and are faced with decisions to navigate, negotiate and invent or re-invent languages, local and global and virtual spaces. The research took place in contexts that include linguistic landscapes, schools, classrooms, neighborhoods and virtual spaces of Australia, Bangladesh, Canada, Japan, Kazakhstan, Mongolia, South Korea and the USA.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLanguage and languagesxGlobalization. 0aLanguage and languages-Globalization. 0aLanguages in contact. 0aMultilingualism. 0aSociolinguistics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Globalization.2bisacsh  aSociolinguistics of globalization.  aSociolinguistics.  abi/multilingualism.  aglobalization.  alinguistic landscape.  alinguistic scapes.  alocalization.  amultilingualism.  atranslingualism.1 aArfin, Jamie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrett, Tyler Andrew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBarrett, Tyler, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCeccato, Tiziana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCupial, Violetta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDovchin, Sender, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDovchin, Sender, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFleming, Kara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvković, Dejan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIzadi, Dariush, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRockell, Kim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aS